{
  "page": "The Dance of the Dragons, A True Telling",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">This article is about the book written by Grand Maester Munkun. For the fifth book in <i>A Song of Ice and Fire</i>, see <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a>. For the Targaryen war for succession, see <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>. For the song, see <a href=\"/index.php/The_Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"The Dance of the Dragons\">The Dance of the Dragons</a>. For the television episode, see <a href=\"/index.php/The_Dance_of_Dragons\" title=\"The Dance of Dragons\">The Dance of Dragons</a>.</div>\n<p><i><b>The Dance of the Dragons, A True Telling</b></i>, at times simply called Munkun's <i><b>True Telling</b></i>,  is a book written by Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Munkun\" title=\"Munkun\">Munkun</a> about the civil war known as the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.  It contains some inaccuracies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Contents\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Contents</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Dance_of_the_Dragons,_A_True_Telling&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Munkun's <i>True Telling</i> was penned about a generation after the events it chronicled. <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">Archmaester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a> regarded it by far the most detailed and authoritative of the many accounts that survived in his day. The exhaustive history drew on many different sources, including maesters' chronicles, memoirs, stewards' records, and interviews with one hundred forty-seven eye witnesses to the events. Much of Munkun's work drew upon the confessions of <a href=\"/index.php/Grand_Maester\" title=\"Grand Maester\">Grand Maester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Orwyle\" title=\"Orwyle\">Orwyle</a>, and eye-witness account, yet one whose author was anxious to portray himself in a favorable light and absolve himself of any misdeeds. Although Orywle himself was thus portrayed too favorably by Munkun by Gyldayn's estimation,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> his writings were nonetheless an invaluable resource to Munkun.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> It may have contained other inaccuracies, such as the illogical claim that <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Byron_Swann\" title=\"Byron Swann\">Byron Swann</a> had attempted to slay <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a>, rather than a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> on the side of the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Orwyle's account was biased in favor of Rhaenyra, however, just as Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Eustace (Dance of the Dragons)\">Eustace</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/The_Reign_of_King_Viserys,_First_of_His_Name,_and_the_Dance_of_the_Dragons_That_Came_After\" title=\"The Reign of King Viserys, First of His Name, and the Dance of the Dragons That Came After\">history of the Dance</a> was biased in favor of Aegon II.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Though <a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">Archmaester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a> believed the titular conflict was more properly termed \"the Dying of the Dragons,\" Munkun's work helped raise the more poetic naming into the pages of history.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Contents\">Contents</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Dance_of_the_Dragons,_A_True_Telling&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Contents\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>It is Munkun's <i>True Telling</i> which reveals that Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Larys_Strong\" title=\"Larys Strong\">Larys Strong</a> made sure that King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> escaped <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> when the city fell to Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> and her forces.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Dance_of_the_Dragons,_A_True_Telling&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Dance_of_the_Dragons,_A_True_Telling&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Byron_Swann_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f0/Byron_Swann_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/250px-Byron_Swann_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"332\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f0/Byron_Swann_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/375px-Byron_Swann_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f0/Byron_Swann_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg/500px-Byron_Swann_%28The_Rise_of_the_Dragon%29.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Byron_Swann_(The_Rise_of_the_Dragon).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Byron_Swann\" title=\"Byron Swann\">Byron Swann</a> faces a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a>, according to <i>True Telling</i> © Tomasz Jedruszek for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i></div></div></div>\n<p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Haldon\" title=\"Haldon\">Haldon</a> Halfmaester asks <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> if he can tell him the name of the knight who tried the same ploy <a href=\"/index.php/Serwyn_of_the_Mirror_Shield\" title=\"Serwyn of the Mirror Shield\">Serwyn of the Mirror Shield</a> used on the dragon <a href=\"/index.php/Urrax\" title=\"Urrax\">Urrax</a> with the dragon <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, Tyrion answers that it was Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Byron_Swann\" title=\"Byron Swann\">Byron Swann</a>, who was roasted for his trouble, but he corrects the halfmaester by stating that the dragon had been <a href=\"/index.php/Syrax\" title=\"Syrax\">Syrax</a>, not Vhagar.  Haldon tells him he is mistaken, mentioning <i>The Dance of the Dragons, A True Telling</i> by Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Munkun\" title=\"Munkun\">Munkun</a> as his source, only to be interrupted by Tyrion, who tells him that Grand Maester Munkun was wrong.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Tyrion explains that Byron's squire saw his master die and wrote of the manner of his death. The squire's account says that the dragon was Syrax, <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>'s she-dragon, which makes much more sense than Munkun's version as Swann was the son of a <a href=\"/index.php/Marcher_lords\" title=\"Marcher lords\">marcher lord</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> was for <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a>.  Vhagar was ridden by Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a>, Aegon’s brother, making it, according to Tyrion, unlogical that Swann would have wanted to slay her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Dance_of_the_Dragons,_A_True_Telling&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_8\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 8\">Chapter 8</a>, Tyrion III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - The Blacks and the Greens.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - The Hooded Hand.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/12432\">Stockholm and Archipelacon Report</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon II.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403123558\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.041 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.072 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 797/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8976/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 3676/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 953/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 3932/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.010/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 4.91 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   60.121      1 -total\n 46.39%   27.890      1 Template:Italic_title\n 23.69%   14.241      8 Template:Ref\n 23.49%   14.122      1 Template:About\n 14.83%    8.918      8 Template:Ref/core\n  4.79%    2.880      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:7571-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403123558 and revision id 332510\n -->\n",
